news.title: GIC to pick up three million sq ft in Bengaluru's Bharatiya City for Rs 2,800 crore
news.para: The deal will see GIC picking up 3 million sq ft of commercial assets in Bhartiya City, a 125-acre township project, from the builder, along with some revenue from its facility management business.

news.title: DS Kulkarni's wife gets bail in Kolhapur misappropriation of funds case
news.para: A case against 62-year-old Hemanti Kulkarni was registered at Kolhapur’s Rajarampuri police station in 2017 over misappropriation of funds collected and deposited by the investors from Kolhapur.

news.title: RBI to get its own office space at Patto Patto in three years
news.para: The RBI building is expected to be completed in three years and could be designed as per Indian Green Building Council (IGBC) norms, officials said.

news.title: Forest department admits land deals in Chikhaldara against rules
news.para: The Maharashtra government, state forest department, and Melghat Tiger Reserve’s (MTR) admission comes on an affidavit filed before the Supreme Court’s Central Empowered Committee (CEC) recently.

news.title: Chandigarh: 12 freehold sites to be up for e-auction from March 14 to 16
news.para: The two nursing home sites are in Sector 51, whereas 10 commercial sites, including booth and SCO are in sectors 33, 36, 39, 42 and 44. Earlier, the estate office started the process of e-auction of eight residential sites on freehold basis.

news.title: Kolkata: Owners can view all property bills at a go on updated portal
news.para: A KMC assessment department official said previously, there were three tabs to view different types of assessment bills: outstanding bills, fresh/supplementary bills and periodic demands (PD) bills.

news.title: Life Mission third phase progressing in Kochi district
news.para: In the third phase, according to former district mission coordinator Ernest C Thomas, the beneficiaries are both landless and those who do not own a house.

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body clears two 119 meter building plans
news.para: Sources in the Ahmedabad Municipal Corporation (AMC) said the two projects will be spread over footprints of 5,000 and 4,800 square metres, respectively.

news.title: Greater Noida authority forms committee to assess structural safety of high-rises
news.para: The committee formed by the authority will take help of IIT Delhi or a similar institute to study the current provision of structural safety certificate.

news.title: Authorities to conduct structural audit of Gurugram's Chintels Paradiso
news.para: While 20 families of Chintel's partially collapsed Tower D were shifted out to temporary accommodations, the option has also been given to 200 flat owners of Towers E, F,G and H, officials said.

news.title: Madhya Pradesh: Satellite survey to identify 20,000 acre land for mega investment region
news.para: The department is also preparing a detailed report on the proposed investment region and international airport by roping in experts and consultants from the aviation and industries sector.

news.title: No explanation for such failure: NGT raps Goa on sand mining notice
news.para: The appellant, Goa river sand protectors’ network (GRSPN), challenged the environment clearance granted by the Goa-SEIAA allowing sand mining in four river stretches in the state.

news.title: Odisha: Construction work in Silk City hit by labour shortage
news.para: Most of the labourers come from Kanishi, Golanthara, Haladiapadar, Randha, Ganju panchayats under Rangeilunda block where the election was held on Friday.

news.title: Telangana government to act tough on undivided land shares and pre-launch offers
news.para: The chief secretary, who is also chairman of RERA, held a meeting with representatives of Credai, Tredai, Telangana Builders Association and other organizations and discussed the development of real estate in individual shares and pre-launch of cases without RERA registration on Friday.

news.title: Land acquisition for Bengaluru metro phase 2B in a stalemate
news.para: One of the crucial elements for this stretch is the construction of a Metro depot at Shettigere. Out of 23 acres of land required, 18 acres have already been transferred by the State Government to the BMRCL.
